1.
Python 3 (3.7-3.8.3)
(programming language)
download and install                  https://www.python.org/downloads/

2.
PyCharm
(IDI)
download and install                  https://www.jetbrains.com/

3.
Git
(a distributed version-control system, vcs)
download and install                  https://git-scm.com/downloads/

4.
GitHub
(a Git repository hosting service)
register                               https://github.com/

5.
Google Chrome
(a browser)
download and install                   https://www.google.com/chrome/

6.
chromedriver
(a driver for the browser)
download and install                  https://chromedriver.chromium.org/downloads

7.
create repo a-project on the GitHub
clone it into project a-project on the desktop(for example)

8.
open a-project on the PyCharm
install Python on this project  PyCharm -> Preferences -> Project:a-project -> Project Interpreter

9.
install on this project: selenium, behave, allure-behave
                                PyCharm -> Preferences -> Project:a-project -> Project Interpreter

10.
for verification execute sample_script.py file